This is one of the most technically sound, well-architected Linux guides available. It does not rely on GUI crutches, perfectly navigates the complexities of an immutable OS, and applies enterprise-grade security concepts (SELinux targeting, ephemeral blind-mounts, systemd transient units) in a digestible way. The 0.5 deduction is solely for the minor risk associated with choosing an SSH port inside the Linux default ephemeral range.
